data.name: formatsLabel.Text
data.value:
Formats to transcode. Transcoding can be done to floating point (32-bit, full resolution, twice the bandwidth) or pcm (16-bit, CD quality). As a rule, you only want floating point if you have 24-bit source files and expect the client to do further processing.
Use MusicBee's audio settings if you would like to use its resampling and upmixing.
If MusicBee's settings, dsp, or replaygain is applied all formats are transcoded. Your client may support replaygain; in that case, it's preferable to not transcode.
